    <stitle>REYCO 101A, 102, 102W SUSPENSIONS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsection id="s03005s" svcsectype="prodspec" division="truck" formnum="CTS-5045S" date="03/31/1996">
        <title>REYCO 101A, 102, 102W SUSPENSIONS</title>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <vendorgroup/>

                <vendor>REYCO</vendor>
                <vendcodegroup/>

                <vendcode>14UCD</vendcode>
                <vendcode>14608</vendcode>
                <vendcode>14627</vendcode>
                <vendcode>14695</vendcode>
                <vendcode>14696</vendcode>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <lev1>
                    <para>On Reyco four-spring tandem suspension systems, the leaf spring assemblies carry the truck
                        axles. The spring assemblies mount at three different locations on each side of the chassis to
                        distribute the load over a large area of the frame rail (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0300501">Figure 1</hotlnk>and
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0300502">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <para>The Reyco 101A Suspension utilizes rigid torque arms to stabilize the springs and to maintain
                        suspension alignment. Refer to
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0300501">Figure 1</hotlnk>.
                    </para>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <figure id="f0300501" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g0300501" filename="../figg03/g0300501.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 1.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1.FRONT OF VEHICLE</callout1>
                            <callout1>2.FRONT SPRING BRACKET</callout1>
                            <callout1>3.EQUALIZER MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                            <callout1>4.REAR SPRING BRACKET AND PLASTIC PAD</callout1>
                            <callout1>5.LEAF SPRING ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                            <callout1>6.RIGID TORQUE ARM</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <figure id="f0300502" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g0300502" filename="../figg03/g0300502.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                        <caption>Figure 2.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1.FRONT OF VEHICLE</callout1>
                            <callout1>2.FRONT SPRING BRACKET</callout1>
                            <callout1>3.EQUALIZER MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                            <callout1>4.REAR SPRING BRACKET AND PLASTIC PAD</callout1>
                            <callout1>5.LEAF SPRING ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                            <callout1>6.ADJUSTABLE TORQUE ARM (REAR)</callout1>
                            <callout1>7.RIGID TORQUE ARM (FRONT)</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <para>The Reyco 102 and 102W Suspensions utilize torque arms (with an adjustable center tube,
                        similar to a turnbuckle) to provide suspension alignment. Refer to
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0300502">Figure 2</hotlnk>, and
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0300503">Figure 3</hotlnk>, and
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0300504">Figure 4</hotlnk>.
                    </para>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <figure id="f0300503" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g0300503" filename="../figg03/g0300503.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                        <caption>Figure 3.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <figure id="f0300504" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g0300504" filename="../figg03/g0300504.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                        <caption>Figure 4.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </lev1>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
